{"word":"G3954 - παῤῥησία - parrhēsía - par-rhay-see'-ah - Bold","slug":"G3954","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">παῤῥησία</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>parrhēsía"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>par-rhay-see'-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bold"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x03C1;&#x0313;&#x03C1;&#x0314;&#x03B7;&#x03C3;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B1; - parrhe&#x0304;sia</b> - <i>par-rhay-see'-ah</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G3956\">G3956</a> and a derivative of <a href=\"#/G4483\">G4483</a>; <i>all</i> out <i>spokenness</i>, that is, <i>frankness</i>, <i>bluntness</i>, <i>publicity</i>; by implication <i>assurance:</i> - bold (X -ly, -ness, -ness of speech), confidence, X freely, X openly, X plainly (-ness)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3955\">G3955</a>"}]}